    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-08-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-08-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="38"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d38">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to Prime
                        Minister <persName type="to">Churchill</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d38fn1">Sent to the United States Naval Attaché, London, via
                        Navy channels.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-08-30">30 August
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Number 611, personal and top secret, from the President for the Prime
                        Minister.<note n="2" xml:id="d38fn2">For the paragraphs of this message
                        omitted here, see <hi rend="italic">post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_222">pp.
                            222</ref>–<ref target="#pg_223">223</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>We can renew our Teheran talk about Trieste and Istria<note n="3" xml:id="d38fn3"
                        >See <ref target="frus1943CairoTehran#pg_493">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, The Conferences at Cairo and
                            Tehran, 1943, pp. 493</ref>, <ref target="frus1943CairoTehran#pg_503"
                            >503</ref>.</note> at <gloss target="#t_Octagon1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Octagon</hi>
                    </gloss>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
